Package net.kemitix.mon

An experiment in creating something similar to a Type-Alias in Java.

Ideas initially lifted from the Design with Types series at https://fsharpforfunandprofit.com/

Author:
Paul Campbell (pcampbell@kemitix.net)
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Functor<T,​F extends Functor<?,​?>>
    The Functor is used for types that can be mapped over.
    ThrowableFunctor<T,​F extends ThrowableFunctor<?,​?>>
    The ThrowableFunctor is used for types that can be mapped over.
    Wrapper<T>
    A wrapper for other types.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Mon<T>
    An almost-monad type-alias.
    TypeAlias<T>
    Type Alias for other types.
    TypeReference<T>
    Helper class to capture a reference to a type.
